the spirit of st. louis is a 1957 aviation biography film in cinemascope from warner bros. , directed by billy wilder , produced by leland hayward , that stars james stewart as charles lindbergh . the screenplay was adapted by charles lederer , wendell mayes , and billy wilder from lindbergh 's 1953 autobiographical account of his historic flight , which won the pulitzer prize in 1954 . along with reminiscences of his early days in aviation , the film 's storyline largely focuses on lindbergh 's lengthy preparation for and finally his history-making transatlantic flight in the purpose-built spirit of st. louis high-wing monoplane . his take off begins at roosevelt field and ends 33-hours later on may 21 , 1927 when he lands safely at le bourget field in paris . the film ends with actual newsreel footage of lindbergh 's ticker tape parade in new york .